-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Thu May 15, 2014 09:33AM EDT
-- None



May 15 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1330 GMT on Thursday:

** Britain's Carphone Warehouse <CPW.L> and Dixons Retail <DXNS.L> have agreed a 3.8 billion pound ($6.4 billion) all-share merger, seeking to tap into the increasing convergence of smartphones and consumer electronics products in people's lives. [ID:nL6N0O11OW]  ** U.S. medical devices company Boston Scientific <BSX.N> on Thursday agreed to buy Bayer AG's <BAYGn.DE> vascular catheter business for $415 million to widen its range of devices to treat clogged blood vessels. [ID:nL6N0O142V]  ** The Dutch Gemini offshore wind farm project signed a three billion euro ($4.1 billion) construction deal with a consortium led by Siemens. [ID:nL6N0O13GF]  ** Erich Kellerhals, the minority owner and founder of Media-Saturn Holding GmbH, has made a new offer to buy back Europe's biggest electronics chain from German retailer Metro AG <MEOG.DE>, alongside other investors, he was quoted as saying on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0O120E]  ** Slovenia has asked potential buyers of its largest telecoms operator Telekom Slovenia <TLSG.LJ> to submit non-binding bids by the start of June, state investment fund SOD said on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0O144S]  ** Deutsche Telekom <DTEGn.DE> is not in any talks about a potential merger, the company told its shareholders on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0O13U7]  ** Hospital operator Kindred Healthcare Inc <KND.N> went hostile with its $533 million offer for Gentiva Health Services Inc <GTIV.O> on Thursday, after Gentiva rejected the bid saying it expected to generate more value as a standalone provider of home healthcare services. [ID:nL3N0O14HJ]  ** U.S. drugmaker Pfizer <PFE.N>, which has made a $106 billion bid approach to British peer AstraZeneca <AZN.L>, has not discussed the proposed deal with European Union regulators, the region's antitrust chief said on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0O04L5] Pfizer's potential takeover of AstraZeneca poses a threat to British science unless the U.S. drugmaker can give more concrete, enforceable guarantees on jobs and investment, politicians scrutinizing the deal said on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0O13XX]** AT&T Inc <T.N> is working with investment bank Lazard Ltd <LAZ.N> as it negotiates a potential takeover of DirecTV <DTV.O>, the top U.S. satellite TV operator, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL1N0O1032]  ** America Movil has submitted its offer to buy the shares of Telekom Austria that the Mexican telecoms giant or its partner, Austrian state holding company OIAG, do not already own. [ID:nL1N0O1079]  ** A joint venture between Britain's Centrica <CNA.L> and Qatar Petroleum has agreed to buy a number of Canadian natural gas assets from Shell <RDSa.L> for C$50 million ($45.85 million)in the entity's first joint acquisition since it was created a year ago. [ID:nL6N0O12MO]  ** The French government has issued a decree allowing it to block foreign takeovers of French firms in "strategic" sectors, throwing up a potential roadblock to General Electric's <GE.N>$16.9 billion bid for Alstom's <ALSO.PA> energy assets. [ID:nL1N0O02AC]  ** Wilmar International Ltd <WLIL.SI> and First Pacific Co Ltd <0142.HK> sweetened a takeover offer for Goodman Fielder Ltd <GFF.AX> to about A$1.37 billion ($1.28 billion), after the Australian food firm rejected an earlier bid as too low. [ID:nL3N0O154J]  ** China's CITIC Pacific Ltd <0267.HK> said it had secured $5.1 billion to help fund the purchase of some $36 billion in assets from its state-owned parent company, as strategic investors lined up to give the landmark deal their blessing. [ID:nL3N0O03RY]  ** Democratic members of the Federal Communications Commission may be divided over how they view the possible Sprint Corp <S.N> merger with T-Mobile US Inc <TMUS.N>, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL3N0O06S0]  ** Bank of Nova Scotia <BNS.TO> said on Wednesday that it would explore options to divest itself of some or all of its 37 percent stake in asset manager CI Financial <CIX.TO> and redeploy the capital elsewhere. [ID:nL1N0O0289]  ** Louisiana-Pacific Corp <LPX.N> has backed away from its planned takeover of Ainsworth Lumber Co <ANS.TO>, blaming the split on demands for more asset sales from Canadian and U.S. regulators, the companies said on Wednesday. [ID:nL1N0O01TV]  ** Insurer American International Group <AIG.N> on Wednesday said it had completed the sale of its aircraft leasing unit to AerCap Holdings <AER.N>, marking the end of years of efforts to sell International Lease Finance Corp. [ID:nL1N0O027A]  ** Grupo BTG Pactual SA, Latin America's largest independent investment bank, is in exclusive talks to buy wealth management firm BSI from Italian insurer Generali SpA <GASI.MI>, according to a statement on Wednesday by Generali. [ID:nL1N0O024Y]  ** Sears Holdings Corp <SHLD.O> said on Wednesday it was looking at selling its 51 percent stake in Sears Canada Inc <SCC.TO>, a move that could trigger a deal for the entire Canadian operation, though a quick and easy sale was seen as unlikely. [ID:nL3N0O041U]  ($1 = 0.5960 British Pounds) ($1 = 1.0906 Canadian Dollars) ($1 = 1.0671 Australian Dollars)